<extrachapter>
  <title>Call for help!</title>
  <section>
  <body>

  <p>
    Due to severe attrition this past year, we now just barely have enough
    manpower to maintain our 350+ packages. This leaves hardly any leftover
    time and energy to extend our offering into new areas, such as natively
    compiled Java packages using gcj, extensively packaging popular
    Eclipse plugins, or creation of a stable and complete J2EE
    development platform.  
  </p>

  <p>
    If you have any interest in helping, consider these options: 
    <ul>
      <li>Helping us to squash <uri link="http://tinyurl.com/n9qb">bugs</uri></li>
      <li><uri link="http://bugs.gentoo.org/">Reporting</uri> any bugs you find.</li>
      <li>Joining our <uri link="http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/lists.xml">gentoo-java mailing list</uri> and asking/answering questions</li> 
      <li>Joining our #gentoo-java channel on irc.freenode.org</li>
      <li>Helping us write documentation</li>
      <li>Spreading the word about Gentoo as a Java development platform</li>
      <li>Improving any existing ebuild</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  </body>
  </section>
</extrachapter>

<extrachapter>
  <title>Experimental Java Projects</title>
 
  <section>
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <body>

  <p>
	Our development of new and exciting stuff is done in the experimental Java 
	subversion repository. You can find it at <uri>https://svn.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/</uri>.
    If you would like to make a checkout of one of these projects, you will,
	of course, have to emerge subversion.
  </p>

  </body>
  </section>  

  <section>
  <title>Experimental Overlay</title>
  <body>
      
  <p>
    The purpose of this experimental overlay is to server as a sandbox 
	for exciting new packages which aren't quite ready for prime-time.
    Some highlights of this overlay include:
  </p>
  <ul>
	<li>
	  modularized <uri link="http://www.jboss.com">JBoss</uri> packages</li>
	<li>
	  <uri link="http://www.springframework.org">the Spring framework</uri>
	</li>
	<li>
	  <uri link="http://maven.apache.org">Maven</uri> built from source.
	</li>
  </ul>

  <pre caption="Check out the experimental overlay"> 
# <i>mkdir -p /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</i>
# <i>svn co https://gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/gentoo-java-experimental /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</i>
<comment>Edit <path>/etc/make.conf</path> and add <path>/usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</path> to PORTDIR_OVERLAY,
i.e. PORTDIR_OVERLAY="${PORTDIR_OVERLAY} /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental"</comment></pre>

  <p>
    Now you should be all set to emerge packages from the experimental tree.
  </p>

  <p>
    You should also update the overlay from time to time.
  </p>
  
<pre caption="Update the experimental overlay">
# <i>cd /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</i>
# <i>svn update</i></pre>

  </body>
  </section>

