  <section>
  <title>Eclipse Plugin Overlay</title>
  <body>
    
  <p>
    One of our users, Chewi, made huge changes to the eclipse eclass. We are 
	now able to build most of the Eclipse plugins which are only in portage 
	as binary packages from source, instead of relying on binary packages.
    <uri link="https://svn.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/chewi-overlay/">chewi-overlay</uri>.
    He also has a <uri link="https://svn.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/chewi-overlay/README.txt">README</uri> explaining the changes.
  </p>

  <note>Some of the plugins in this overlay require packages only found in the experimental overlay!</note>

  <pre caption="Check out the Eclipse overlay">
# <i>mkdir -p /usr/local/overlays/chewi-overlay</i>
# <i>svn co https://gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/chewi-overlay /usr/local/overlays/chewi-overlay</i>
<comment>Edit <path>/etc/make.conf</path> and add <path>/usr/local/overlays/chewi-overlay</path> to PORTDIR_OVERLAY,
i.e. PORTDIR_OVERLAY="${PORTDIR_OVERLAY} /usr/local/overlays/chewi-overlay"</comment></pre>

  <p>You should also update the overlay occaisionally.</p>
<pre caption="Update the Eclipse overlay"># <i>cd /usr/local/overlays/chewi-overlay</i>
# <i>svn update</i></pre>


  </body>
  </section>

  <section>
  <title>java-config-ng</title>
  <body>
	<p>
      Compnerd started java-config-ng as an attempt to improve the current 
	  java-config.  Yet again, it can found in the svn repository,
	  <uri link="https://svn.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/java-config-ng/">here</uri>.
	</p>
    <p>
      axxo started a branch to add functionality to support things needed 
      for the 1.5 overlay and generally make things work. It can be found
      <uri link="http://gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/java-config-ng/branches/axxo/">here</uri>.
    </p>

  </body>
  </section>
